      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-base-content mt-8 mb-4">Personal Relationships and Radical Honesty</h3>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        The principle extends beyond professional relationships to close personal ones. Your closest friends, romantic 
        partners, and family members who genuinely want to support you can only do so effectively if they understand 
        your real situation. This doesn't mean sharing everything with everyone—it means being selective about who 
        gets your trust, then being complete in that trust.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        The key distinction is between allies and acquaintances. Allies are people who have demonstrated consistent 
        support, maintained confidentiality, and shown up during difficult times. These relationships can handle 
        radical honesty and become stronger because of it. Acquaintances should receive polite but limited information.
      </p>

